{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I'd like to talk about is really the biggest problems in the world."},{"time":4000,"text":"I'm not going to talk about \"The Skeptical Environmentalist\" --"},{"time":6000,"text":"probably that's also a good choice."},{"time":8000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9000,"text":"But I am going talk about: what are the big problems in the world?"},{"time":12000,"text":"And I must say, before I go on, I should ask every one of you"},{"time":15000,"text":"to try and get out pen and paper"},{"time":17000,"text":"because I'm actually going to ask you to help me to look at how we do that."},{"time":20000,"text":"So get out your pen and paper."},{"time":22000,"text":"Bottom line is, there is a lot of problems out there in the world."},{"time":24000,"text":"I'm just going to list some of them."},{"time":26000,"text":"There are 800 million people starving."},{"time":28000,"text":"There's a billion people without clean drinking water."},{"time":30000,"text":"Two billion people without sanitation."},{"time":32000,"text":"There are several million people dying of HIV and AIDS."},{"time":35000,"text":"The lists go on and on."},{"time":37000,"text":"There's two billions of people who will be severely affected by climate change -- so on."},{"time":42000,"text":"There are many, many problems out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"In an ideal world, we would solve them all, but we don't."},{"time":48000,"text":"We don't actually solve all problems."},{"time":50000,"text":"And if we do not, the question I think we need to ask ourselves --"},{"time":54000,"text":"and that's why it's on the economy session -- is to say,"},{"time":57000,"text":"if we don't do all things, we really have to start asking ourselves,"},{"time":60000,"text":"which ones should we solve first?"},{"time":62000,"text":"And that's the question I'd like to ask you."},{"time":64000,"text":"If we had say, 50 billion dollars over the next four years to spend"},{"time":69000,"text":"to do good in this world, where should we spend it?"},{"time":72000,"text":"We identified 10 of the biggest challenges in the world,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and I will just briefly read them:"},{"time":77000,"text":"climate change, communicable diseases, conflicts, education,"},{"time":79000,"text":"financial instability, governance and corruption,"},{"time":81000,"text":"malnutrition and hunger, population migration,"},{"time":84000,"text":"sanitation and water, and subsidies and trade barriers."},{"time":87000,"text":"We believe that these in many ways"},{"time":89000,"text":"encompass the biggest problems in the world."},{"time":91000,"text":"The obvious question would be to ask,"},{"time":93000,"text":"what do you think are the biggest things?"},{"time":95000,"text":"Where should we start on solving these problems?"},{"time":98000,"text":"But that's a wrong problem to ask."},{"time":100000,"text":"That was actually the problem that was asked in Davos in January."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"But of course, there's a problem in asking people to focus on problems."},{"time":106000,"text":"Because we can't solve problems."},{"time":109000,"text":"Surely the biggest problem we have in the world is that we all die."},{"time":112000,"text":"But we don't have a technology to solve that, right?"},{"time":114000,"text":"So the point is not to prioritize problems,"},{"time":117000,"text":"but the point is to prioritize solutions to problems."},{"time":121000,"text":"And that would be -- of course that gets a little more complicated."},{"time":124000,"text":"To climate change that would be like Kyoto."},{"time":126000,"text":"To communicable diseases, it might be health clinics or mosquito nets."},{"time":129000,"text":"To conflicts, it would be U.N.'s peacekeeping forces, and so on."},{"time":132000,"text":"The point that I would like to ask you to try to do,"},{"time":137000,"text":"is just in 30 seconds -- and I know this is in a sense"},{"time":140000,"text":"an impossible task -- write down what you think"},{"time":142000,"text":"is probably some of the top priorities."},{"time":144000,"text":"And also -- and that's, of course, where economics gets evil --"},{"time":147000,"text":"to put down what are the things we should not do, first."},{"time":150000,"text":"What should be at the bottom of the list?"},{"time":152000,"text":"Please, just take 30 seconds, perhaps talk to your neighbor,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and just figure out what should be the top priorities"},{"time":157000,"text":"and the bottom priorities of the solutions that we have"},{"time":159000,"text":"to the world's biggest issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"The amazing part of this process -- and of course, I mean,"},{"time":164000,"text":"I would love to -- I only have 18 minutes,"},{"time":166000,"text":"I've already given you quite a substantial amount of my time, right?"},{"time":168000,"text":"I'd love to go into, and get you to think about this process,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and that's actually what we did."},{"time":174000,"text":"And I also strongly encourage you,"},{"time":176000,"text":"and I'm sure we'll also have these discussions afterwards,"},{"time":178000,"text":"to think about, how do we actually prioritize?"},{"time":180000,"text":"Of course, you have to ask yourself,"},{"time":182000,"text":"why on Earth was such a list never done before?"},{"time":184000,"text":"And one reason is that prioritization is incredibly uncomfortable."},{"time":189000,"text":"Nobody wants to do this."},{"time":191000,"text":"Of course, every organization would love to be on the top of such a list."},{"time":194000,"text":"But every organization would also hate to be not on the top of the list."},{"time":197000,"text":"And since there are many more not-number-one spots on the list"},{"time":201000,"text":"than there is number ones, it makes perfect sense"},{"time":204000,"text":"not to want to do such a list."},{"time":206000,"text":"We've had the U.N. for almost 60 years,"},{"time":208000,"text":"yet we've never actually made a fundamental list"},{"time":211000,"text":"of all the big things that we can do in the world,"},{"time":213000,"text":"and said, which of them should we do first?"},{"time":216000,"text":"So it doesn't mean that we are not prioritizing --"},{"time":219000,"text":"any decision is a prioritization, so of course we are still prioritizing,"},{"time":223000,"text":"if only implicitly -- and that's unlikely to be as good"},{"time":226000,"text":"as if we actually did the prioritization,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and went in and talked about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"So what I'm proposing is really to say that we have,"},{"time":232000,"text":"for a very long time, had a situation when we've had a menu of choices."},{"time":236000,"text":"There are many, many things we can do out there,"},{"time":238000,"text":"but we've not had the prices, nor the sizes."},{"time":241000,"text":"We have not had an idea."},{"time":243000,"text":"Imagine going into a restaurant and getting this big menu card,"},{"time":246000,"text":"but you have no idea what the price is."},{"time":248000,"text":"You know, you have a pizza; you've no idea what the price is."},{"time":250000,"text":"It could be at one dollar; it could be 1,000 dollars."},{"time":252000,"text":"It could be a family-size pizza;"},{"time":254000,"text":"it could be a very individual-size pizza, right?"},{"time":256000,"text":"We'd like to know these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"And that is what the Copenhagen Consensus is really trying to do --"},{"time":260000,"text":"to try to put prices on these issues."},{"time":263000,"text":"And so basically, this has been the Copenhagen Consensus' process."},{"time":266000,"text":"We got 30 of the world's best economists, three in each area."},{"time":270000,"text":"So we have three of world's top economists write about climate change."},{"time":273000,"text":"What can we do? What will be the cost"},{"time":276000,"text":"and what will be the benefit of that?"},{"time":277000,"text":"Likewise in communicable diseases."},{"time":279000,"text":"Three of the world's top experts saying, what can we do?"},{"time":282000,"text":"What would be the price?"},{"time":283000,"text":"What should we do about it, and what will be the outcome?"},{"time":286000,"text":"And so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"Then we had some of the world's top economists,"},{"time":289000,"text":"eight of the world's top economists, including three Nobel Laureates,"},{"time":293000,"text":"meet in Copenhagen in May 2004."},{"time":296000,"text":"We called them the \"dream team.\""},{"time":298000,"text":"The Cambridge University prefects decided to call them"},{"time":301000,"text":"the Real Madrid of economics."},{"time":303000,"text":"That works very well in Europe, but it doesn't really work over here."},{"time":305000,"text":"And what they basically did was come out with a prioritized list."},{"time":309000,"text":"And then you ask, why economists?"},{"time":311000,"text":"And of course, I'm very happy you asked that question -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":313000,"text":"because that's a very good question."},{"time":315000,"text":"The point is, of course, if you want to know about malaria,"},{"time":318000,"text":"you ask a malaria expert."},{"time":320000,"text":"If you want to know about climate, you ask a climatologist."},{"time":322000,"text":"But if you want to know which of the two you should deal with first,"},{"time":325000,"text":"you can't ask either of them, because that's not what they do."},{"time":328000,"text":"That is what economists do."},{"time":330000,"text":"They prioritize."},{"time":331000,"text":"They make that in some ways disgusting task of saying, which one should we do first,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and which one should we do afterwards?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"So this is the list, and this is the one I'd like to share with you."},{"time":341000,"text":"Of course, you can also see it on the website,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and we'll also talk about it more, I'm sure, as the day goes on."},{"time":346000,"text":"They basically came up with a list where they said"},{"time":348000,"text":"there were bad projects -- basically, projects"},{"time":351000,"text":"where if you invest a dollar, you get less than a dollar back."},{"time":354000,"text":"Then there's fair projects, good projects and very good projects."},{"time":358000,"text":"And of course, it's the very good projects we should start doing."},{"time":360000,"text":"I'm going to go from backwards"},{"time":362000,"text":"so that we end up with the best projects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"These were the bad projects."},{"time":366000,"text":"As you might see the bottom of the list was climate change."},{"time":370000,"text":"This offends a lot of people, and that's probably one of the things"},{"time":374000,"text":"where people will say I shouldn't come back, either."},{"time":376000,"text":"And I'd like to talk about that, because that's really curious."},{"time":378000,"text":"Why is it it came up?"},{"time":380000,"text":"And I'll actually also try to get back to this"},{"time":382000,"text":"because it's probably one of the things"},{"time":384000,"text":"that we'll disagree with on the list that you wrote down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"The reason why they came up with saying that Kyoto --"},{"time":389000,"text":"or doing something more than Kyoto -- is a bad deal"},{"time":391000,"text":"is simply because it's very inefficient."},{"time":393000,"text":"It's not saying that global warming is not happening."},{"time":395000,"text":"It's not saying that it's not a big problem."},{"time":397000,"text":"But it's saying that what we can do about it"},{"time":399000,"text":"is very little, at a very high cost."},{"time":402000,"text":"What they basically show us, the average of all macroeconomic models,"},{"time":406000,"text":"is that Kyoto, if everyone agreed, would cost about 150 billion dollars a year."},{"time":411000,"text":"That's a substantial amount of money."},{"time":413000,"text":"That's two to three times the global development aid"},{"time":415000,"text":"that we give the Third World every year."},{"time":417000,"text":"Yet it would do very little good."},{"time":419000,"text":"All models show it will postpone warming for about six years in 2100."},{"time":423000,"text":"So the guy in Bangladesh who gets a flood in 2100 can wait until 2106."},{"time":427000,"text":"Which is a little good, but not very much good."},{"time":429000,"text":"So the idea here really is to say, well, we've spent a lot of money doing a little good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"And just to give you a sense of reference,"},{"time":436000,"text":"the U.N. actually estimate that for half that amount,"},{"time":438000,"text":"for about 75 billion dollars a year,"},{"time":440000,"text":"we could solve all major basic problems in the world."},{"time":443000,"text":"We could give clean drinking water, sanitation, basic healthcare"},{"time":446000,"text":"and education to every single human being on the planet."},{"time":449000,"text":"So we have to ask ourselves, do we want to spend twice the amount"},{"time":453000,"text":"on doing very little good?"},{"time":454000,"text":"Or half the amount on doing an amazing amount of good?"},{"time":457000,"text":"And that is really why it becomes a bad project."},{"time":460000,"text":"It's not to say that if we had all the money in the world, we wouldn't want to do it."},{"time":463000,"text":"But it's to say, when we don't, it's just simply not our first priority."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"The fair projects -- notice I'm not going to comment on all these --"},{"time":470000,"text":"but communicable diseases, scale of basic health services -- just made it,"},{"time":474000,"text":"simply because, yes, scale of basic health services is a great thing."},{"time":477000,"text":"It would do a lot of good, but it's also very, very costly."},{"time":480000,"text":"Again, what it tells us is suddenly"},{"time":482000,"text":"we start thinking about both sides of the equation."},{"time":484000,"text":"If you look at the good projects, a lot of sanitation and water projects came in."},{"time":488000,"text":"Again, sanitation and water is incredibly important,"},{"time":490000,"text":"but it also costs a lot of infrastructure."},{"time":493000,"text":"So I'd like to show you the top four priorities"},{"time":495000,"text":"which should be at least the first ones that we deal with"},{"time":498000,"text":"when we talk about how we should deal with the problems in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"The fourth best problem is malaria -- dealing with malaria."},{"time":505000,"text":"The incidence of malaria is about a couple of [million] people get infected every year."},{"time":509000,"text":"It might even cost up towards a percentage point of GDP"},{"time":513000,"text":"every year for affected nations."},{"time":515000,"text":"If we invested about 13 billion dollars over the next four years,"},{"time":519000,"text":"we could bring that incidence down to half."},{"time":521000,"text":"We could avoid about 500,000 people dying,"},{"time":524000,"text":"but perhaps more importantly, we could avoid about a [million] people"},{"time":527000,"text":"getting infected every year."},{"time":528000,"text":"We would significantly increase their ability"},{"time":530000,"text":"to deal with many of the other problems that they have to deal with --"},{"time":533000,"text":"of course, in the long run, also to deal with global warming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537000,"text":"This third best one was free trade."},{"time":540000,"text":"Basically, the model showed that if we could get free trade,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and especially cut subsidies in the U.S. and Europe,"},{"time":546000,"text":"we could basically enliven the global economy"},{"time":550000,"text":"to an astounding number of about 2,400 billion dollars a year,"},{"time":554000,"text":"half of which would accrue to the Third World."},{"time":556000,"text":"Again, the point is to say that we could actually pull"},{"time":559000,"text":"two to three hundred million people out of poverty,"},{"time":562000,"text":"very radically fast, in about two to five years."},{"time":565000,"text":"That would be the third best thing we could do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"The second best thing would be to focus on malnutrition."},{"time":571000,"text":"Not just malnutrition in general, but there's a very cheap way"},{"time":574000,"text":"of dealing with malnutrition, namely, the lack of micronutrients."},{"time":577000,"text":"Basically, about half of the world's population is lacking in"},{"time":580000,"text":"iron, zinc, iodine and vitamin A."},{"time":582000,"text":"If we invest about 12 billion dollars,"},{"time":584000,"text":"we could make a severe inroad into that problem."},{"time":587000,"text":"That would be the second best investment that we could do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"And the very best project would be to focus on HIV/AIDS."},{"time":595000,"text":"Basically, if we invest 27 billion dollars over the next eight years,"},{"time":599000,"text":"we could avoid 28 new million cases of HIV/AIDS."},{"time":603000,"text":"Again, what this does and what it focuses on is saying"},{"time":607000,"text":"there are two very different ways that we can deal with HIV/AIDS."},{"time":610000,"text":"One is treatment; the other one is prevention."},{"time":613000,"text":"And again, in an ideal world, we would do both."},{"time":616000,"text":"But in a world where we don't do either, or don't do it very well,"},{"time":619000,"text":"we have to at least ask ourselves where should we invest first."},{"time":623000,"text":"And treatment is much, much more expensive than prevention."},{"time":626000,"text":"So basically, what this focuses on is saying, we can do a lot more"},{"time":630000,"text":"by investing in prevention."},{"time":632000,"text":"Basically for the amount of money that we spend,"},{"time":634000,"text":"we can do X amount of good in treatment,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and 10 times as much good in prevention."},{"time":640000,"text":"So again, what we focus on is prevention rather than treatment,"},{"time":643000,"text":"at first rate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"What this really does is that it makes us think about our priorities."},{"time":648000,"text":"I'd like to have you look at your priority list and say,"},{"time":652000,"text":"did you get it right?"},{"time":654000,"text":"Or did you get close to what we came up with here?"},{"time":656000,"text":"Well, of course, one of the things is climate change again."},{"time":660000,"text":"I find a lot of people find it very, very unlikely that we should do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"We should also do climate change,"},{"time":665000,"text":"if for no other reason, simply because it's such a big problem."},{"time":668000,"text":"But of course, we don't do all problems."},{"time":671000,"text":"There are many problems out there in the world."},{"time":673000,"text":"And what I want to make sure of is, if we actually focus on problems,"},{"time":677000,"text":"that we focus on the right ones."},{"time":679000,"text":"The ones where we can do a lot of good rather than a little good."},{"time":682000,"text":"And I think, actually -- Thomas Schelling,"},{"time":685000,"text":"one of the participants in the dream team, he put it very, very well."},{"time":689000,"text":"One of things that people forget, is that in 100 years,"},{"time":692000,"text":"when we're talking about most of the climate change impacts will be,"},{"time":695000,"text":"people will be much, much richer."},{"time":697000,"text":"Even the most pessimistic impact scenarios of the U.N."},{"time":701000,"text":"estimate that the average person in the developing world in 2100"},{"time":704000,"text":"will be about as rich as we are today."},{"time":706000,"text":"Much more likely, they will be two to four times richer than we are."},{"time":710000,"text":"And of course, we'll be even richer than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"But the point is to say, when we talk about saving people,"},{"time":716000,"text":"or helping people in Bangladesh in 2100,"},{"time":719000,"text":"we're not talking about a poor Bangladeshi."},{"time":721000,"text":"We're actually talking about a fairly rich Dutch guy."},{"time":723000,"text":"And so the real point, of course, is to say,"},{"time":725000,"text":"do we want to spend a lot of money helping a little,"},{"time":729000,"text":"100 years from now, a fairly rich Dutch guy?"},{"time":731000,"text":"Or do we want to help real poor people, right now, in Bangladesh,"},{"time":736000,"text":"who really need the help, and whom we can help very, very cheaply?"},{"time":739000,"text":"Or as Schelling put it, imagine if you were a rich -- as you will be --"},{"time":744000,"text":"a rich Chinese, a rich Bolivian, a rich Congolese, in 2100,"},{"time":749000,"text":"thinking back on 2005, and saying, \"How odd that they cared so much"},{"time":755000,"text":"about helping me a little bit through climate change,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and cared so fairly little about helping my grandfather"},{"time":763000,"text":"and my great grandfather, whom they could have helped so much more,"},{"time":766000,"text":"and who needed the help so much more?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"So I think that really does tell us why it is"},{"time":772000,"text":"we need to get our priorities straight."},{"time":774000,"text":"Even if it doesn't accord to the typical way we see this problem."},{"time":777000,"text":"Of course, that's mainly because climate change has good pictures."},{"time":782000,"text":"We have, you know, \"The Day After Tomorrow\" -- it looks great, right?"},{"time":785000,"text":"It's a good film in the sense that"},{"time":788000,"text":"I certainly want to see it, right, but don't expect Emmerich"},{"time":791000,"text":"to cast Brad Pitt in his next movie"},{"time":794000,"text":"digging latrines in Tanzania or something. (Laughter)"},{"time":796000,"text":"It just doesn't make for as much of a movie."},{"time":798000,"text":"So in many ways, I think of the Copenhagen Consensus"},{"time":800000,"text":"and the whole discussion of priorities"},{"time":802000,"text":"as a defense for boring problems."},{"time":805000,"text":"To make sure that we realize it's not about making us feel good."},{"time":809000,"text":"It's not about making things that have the most media attention,"},{"time":814000,"text":"but it's about making places where we can actually do the most good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"The other objections, I think, that are important to say,"},{"time":820000,"text":"is that I'm somehow -- or we are somehow -- positing a false choice."},{"time":824000,"text":"Of course, we should do all things,"},{"time":826000,"text":"in an ideal world -- I would certainly agree."},{"time":828000,"text":"I think we should do all things, but we don't."},{"time":830000,"text":"In 1970, the developed world decided we were going to spend"},{"time":834000,"text":"twice as much as we did, right now, than in 1970, on the developing world."},{"time":840000,"text":"Since then our aid has halved."},{"time":842000,"text":"So it doesn't look like we're actually on the path"},{"time":845000,"text":"of suddenly solving all big problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"Likewise, people are also saying, but what about the Iraq war?"},{"time":850000,"text":"You know, we spend 100 billion dollars --"},{"time":852000,"text":"why don't we spend that on doing good in the world?"},{"time":854000,"text":"I'm all for that."},{"time":855000,"text":"If any one of you guys can talk Bush into doing that, that's fine."},{"time":857000,"text":"But the point, of course, is still to say,"},{"time":859000,"text":"if you get another 100 billion dollars,"},{"time":861000,"text":"we still want to spend that in the best possible way, don't we?"},{"time":864000,"text":"So the real issue here is to get ourselves back"},{"time":866000,"text":"and think about what are the right priorities."},{"time":868000,"text":"I should just mention briefly, is this really the right list that we got out?"},{"time":872000,"text":"You know, when you ask the world's best economists,"},{"time":875000,"text":"you inevitably end up asking old, white American men."},{"time":878000,"text":"And they're not necessarily, you know,"},{"time":880000,"text":"great ways of looking at the entire world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"So we actually invited 80 young people from all over the world"},{"time":886000,"text":"to come and solve the same problem."},{"time":888000,"text":"The only two requirements were that they were studying at the university,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and they spoke English."},{"time":894000,"text":"The majority of them were, first, from developing countries."},{"time":897000,"text":"They had all the same material but they could go vastly"},{"time":899000,"text":"outside the scope of discussion, and they certainly did,"},{"time":902000,"text":"to come up with their own lists."},{"time":904000,"text":"And the surprising thing was that the list was very similar --"},{"time":906000,"text":"with malnutrition and diseases at the top"},{"time":909000,"text":"and climate change at the bottom."},{"time":911000,"text":"We've done this many other times."},{"time":912000,"text":"There's been many other seminars and university students, and different things."},{"time":915000,"text":"They all come out with very much the same list."},{"time":918000,"text":"And that gives me great hope, really, in saying that I do believe"},{"time":922000,"text":"that there is a path ahead to get us to start thinking about priorities,"},{"time":927000,"text":"and saying, what is the important thing in the world?"},{"time":929000,"text":"Of course, in an ideal world, again we'd love to do everything."},{"time":932000,"text":"But if we don't do it, then we can start thinking about where should we start?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":936000,"text":"I see the Copenhagen Consensus as a process."},{"time":938000,"text":"We did it in 2004,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and we hope to assemble many more people,"},{"time":941000,"text":"getting much better information for 2008, 2012."},{"time":945000,"text":"Map out the right path for the world --"},{"time":947000,"text":"but also to start thinking about political triage."},{"time":950000,"text":"To start thinking about saying, \"Let's do"},{"time":952000,"text":"not the things where we can do very little at a very high cost,"},{"time":955000,"text":"not the things that we don't know how to do,"},{"time":957000,"text":"but let's do the great things where we can do an enormous"},{"time":960000,"text":"amount of good, at very low cost, right now.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"At the end of the day, you can disagree"},{"time":966000,"text":"with the discussion of how we actually prioritize these,"},{"time":968000,"text":"but we have to be honest and frank about saying,"},{"time":971000,"text":"if there's some things we do, there are other things we don't do."},{"time":974000,"text":"If we worry too much about some things,"},{"time":976000,"text":"we end by not worrying about other things."},{"time":978000,"text":"So I hope this will help us make better priorities,"},{"time":980000,"text":"and think about how we better work for the world."},{"time":982000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}